File: A total of 634,996 tests have been conducted to date with 29,005 tests recorded since the last report. JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department has reported 28 new COVID-19 deaths. This takes the death toll to 552. The department's latest report shows that 1,673 new infections have been confirmed, taking the cumulative number of confirmed cases to 25,937. READ: Unpacking SA's COVID-19 numbers with the NICD A total of 634,996 tests have been conducted to date with 29,005 tests recorded since the last report. The recoveries to date are 13,451 which the department said translates to a recovery rate of 52 percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.